1) generate a private key:
openssl genrsa -out krish.key 2048

2) certificate singing request with the user:
openssl req -new -key krish.key -out krish.csr -subj "/CN=krish/O=devops"

3) use certifaicate singing request and singing it with certificate signing authority:
openssl x509 -req -CA ~/path/ca.crt -CAkey ~/path/ca.key -CAcreateserial -days 730 -in krish.csr -out krish.crt

4) now using this certificate to create user in kubernetes cluster:
kubectl config set-credentials krish --client-certificate=krish.crt --client-key=krish.key

5) now setting context for this newly added user:
kebectl config set-context krish-kind --cluster=docker-desktop --user=krish

